apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: middleware-to-mysql
  namespace: default
spec:
  podSelector:
    matchLabels:
      app: mysql
  ingress:
  - from:
    - podSelector:
        matchLabels:
          app: middleware

Egress policies are the policies that are used to control the traffic that leaves the pod. It helps to limit or allow the outbound traffic from the pods.


apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: jonin-to-genin
  namespace: jonin
spec:
  policyTypes:
  - Egress
  egress:
  - to:
    - podSelector:
        matchLabels:
          rank: genin
      namespaceSelector:
        matchLabels:
          kubernetes.io/metadata.name: genin




apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: hokage-allow
  namespace: default
spec:
  podSelector:
    matchLabels:
      rank: hokage
  policyTypes:
  - Egress
  egress:
  - to:
    - podSelector:
        matchLabels:
          rank: genin
      namespaceSelector:
        matchLabels:
          kubernetes.io/metadata.name: genin
    - podSelector:
        matchLabels:
          rank: jonin
      namespaceSelector:
        matchLabels:
           kubernetes.io/metadata.name: jonin
